# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  opencmdb — .gitignore
#
#  Written BEFORE `git init`, deliberately. This project ships binaries to
#  strangers via Docker Hub; the first commit is the wrong place to discover
#  what should not have been in it.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── SECRETS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# D27: the master key lives OUTSIDE the data volume, in a separate DSM shared
# folder. It has no business anywhere near the tree. D63: a secret reaches a
# dev tool on STDIN — never the environment, never an argument, never a file.
# These lines are a net under a rule, not the rule.
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
secrets/
.secrets/
master.key
*.age
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Harness-written. This is the file that recorded a UniFi password verbatim on
# 2026-07-16 — inside the tree, before git existed. It is ignored on purpose.
.claude/settings.local.json

# ── RUST ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb

# Cargo.lock is COMMITTED — not an oversight.
# "We ship binaries to strangers via Docker Hub. Nothing resolves on the fly at
#  build time." Same doctrine as the committed CSS. Do not add Cargo.lock here.

# ── ASSETS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# assets/app.css is COMMITTED (D55) — generated by `cargo xtask css`, never by
# build.rs. A build that regenerates it would contradict the committed CSS and
# would fail on a machine without the Tailwind CLI. Do NOT ignore app.css.
#
# The pinned Tailwind standalone binary itself is a tool, not a source:
/tools/tailwindcss*
tailwindcss-linux-*
tailwindcss-macos-*

# ── FIXTURES ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# fixtures/ is COMMITTED — versioned artefacts, not tests (D19/D56).
# The JSONL oracle, the ~50 YAML traps and MANIFEST.toml all belong in git.
# Do NOT ignore fixtures/.
#
# What must NEVER enter: real captures containing MACs, hostnames or the
# topology of a real network. "For an open-source project this is
# disqualifying. Not debatable." (D19)
fixtures/capture/**/raw-*
fixtures/**/*.local.*
probe*.py
probe-*.json

# ── LOCAL / TRANSIENT ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
/data/
/backups/
*.bak
*.tmp
*.swp
*~

# ── OS / EDITOR ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
!.vscode/extensions.json

# ── INSTALLER-MANAGED VENDOR (decided 2026-07-17) ───────────────────────────
# BMad framework and installed skills are regenerated by the installer and declared
# read-only in CLAUDE.md — versioning files the installer overwrites is noise, and it
# drowns the code 60:1. The project's crown jewels (the planning artefacts) live in
# _bmad-output/ and ARE tracked. Config overrides in _bmad/custom/ are intentionally
# committed (team-scoped), so they are re-included below.
.claude/
_bmad/
!_bmad/custom/
!_bmad/custom/**

# ── RUNTIME LOGS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Daily-rotating file logs from the container (docker-compose mounts docker/log).
# They carry observed IPs/hostnames — runtime artifacts, never committed.
docker/log/
